&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete quality assessments for emerging and innovative technology pathways, including developing evaluation frameworks, often in coordination with other subject matter experts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess quality parameters at the project level, including project design, baseline setting, additionality, leakage, permanence, monitoring plans, quantification approaches, uncertainty treatment, and delivery risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and lead due diligence process for investing in impactful non-CO2 projects&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support portfolio management by identifying technical underperformance drivers, implementation bottlenecks, issuance risks, and mitigation measures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and interpret evolving carbon market integrity frameworks, including ICVCM CCP, ratings agency frameworks and criteria, and broader market expectations on project quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain information systems that interpret and share findings with relevant internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with and maintain productive relationships with project developers and other key stakeholders&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-driven capability to stay apprised of the frontier in science in various technologies and industries&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with RFP responses and provide on-call subject matter expertise as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex GHG accounting and project science into accessible materials for internal stakeholders and external audiences, including professional working groups&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop thought leadership and science communications that position Rubicon Carbon as a leader in the SPE credit markets&lt;/li&gt;
